Build a full-stack web application called “ClosetCycle” — a coordinator-managed clothing redistribution platform that connects people who want to donate unused clothes with people who need affordable or free clothing.

## 🎯 Core Goal
Reduce textile waste and enable affordable clothing access using a simple, coordinator-driven system instead of forcing all users to adopt complex apps.

---

## 👥 User Roles
1. Donor (people giving clothes)
2. Receiver (people browsing and taking clothes)
3. Coordinator (admin managing inventory, approvals, and logistics)

---

## 🧩 Key Features

### 1. Donor Flow (Simple UX)
- Donor submits clothes via:
  - Form (name, phone, item type, size, condition)
  - Upload images (multiple)
- Option: “Submit via WhatsApp” (simulate with button or API placeholder)
- No login required (keep it frictionless)

---

### 2. Coordinator Dashboard (Core System)
- Secure login for coordinator
- Features:
  - View all submitted clothes
  - Approve / reject items
  - Categorize items:
    - Type (shirt, jeans, kurta, etc.)
    - Size (S, M, L, XL)
    - Gender category
    - Condition (new, lightly used)
  - Upload approved items to public catalog
  - Manage orders/reservations
  - Track inventory status (available / reserved / delivered)

---

### 3. Receiver Flow
- Browse clothing catalog
- Filters:
  - Size
  - Category
  - Gender
  - Price (free / low cost)
- View item details:
  - Images
  - Description
  - Condition
- Reserve item
- Option for:
  - Pickup
  - Delivery (mocked)

---

### 4. Smart Features (Important)
- Basic recommendation system:
  - Show “You may also like” based on selected items
- Bundle suggestion:
  - Suggest “3 items for ₹X” to clear inventory faster

---

### 5. Order System
- Receivers can:
  - Add items to cart
  - Reserve items
- Coordinator confirms and updates status

---

## 🧠 Design Principles
- Keep donor experience extremely simple (no login)
- Focus complexity on coordinator dashboard
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Clean, minimal UI

---

## 🎨 UI Requirements
- Modern card-based layout for clothes
- Dashboard with sidebar navigation
- Use clear tags (size, condition, category)
- Add sustainability-themed colors (green, beige, white)

